ciscoFabricMcastApplMIB.name: ciscoFabricMcastApplMIB

revisions.description: Initial version of this MIB module.

ciscoFabricMcastApplMIB.contactinfo: Cisco Systems Customer Service Postal: 170 W. Tasman Drive San Jose, CA 95134 USA Tel: +1 800 553-NETS E-mail: cs-fabric@cisco.com
ciscoFabricMcastApplMIB.description: Fabric multicast resource MIB module. This MIB module is used for managing/tracking the fabric multicast resource application related information. Acronyms and terms: FGID - Fabric Multicast Group Identifier.

cfmaApplTable.name: cfmaApplTable
cfmaApplTable.description: This table contains fabric multicast resource usage for a particular fabric multicast client application.

cfmaApplEntry.name: cfmaApplEntry
cfmaApplEntry.description: The information regarding a single application that uses fabric multicast resource in a logical router. An entry of this table is created when a fabric multicast client application is registered to fabric software for the use of fabric multicast resource from a logical router. A logical router is identified by the value of mib-2 in entLogicalType object of ENTITY-MIB. An entry of this table is deleted when a fabric multicast client application unregistered the use of fabric multicast resource.

cfmaApplId.name: cfmaApplId
cfmaApplId.description: An unique value, greater than zero, for each fabric client application that uses fabric multicast resource.

cfmaApplName.name: cfmaApplName
cfmaApplName.description: The name of this fabric multicast client application.

cfmaApplInuseFgids.name: cfmaApplInuseFgids
cfmaApplInuseFgids.description: The number of FGIDs that are currently in use by this application.

cfmaApplHighWaterInuseFGIDs.name: cfmaApplHighWaterInuseFGIDs
cfmaApplHighWaterInuseFGIDs.description: The highest number of FGIDs that was in use by this application.

cfmaApplPoolId.name: cfmaApplPoolId
cfmaApplPoolId.description: The fabric multicast resource pool id for the resource pool which is used by this application.

cfmaMIBCompliance.name: cfmaMIBCompliance
cfmaMIBCompliance.description: The compliance statement for entities which implement the CISCO-FABRIC-MCAST-APPL-MIB

cfmaApplGroup.name: cfmaApplGroup
cfmaApplGroup.description: A collection of objects providing information for the applications that use the fabric multicast resource.
